Your reasoning is flawed, gnome.  Tier'dal are diffrent creatures.  We are not Koda'dal with a blue tint to our skin and a perchant for violence... anymore then we are tall blue gnomes.  You assume, based on who and what you are, that we share similar ways of thinking.  We do not.  You may credit our diffrences to breeding, nuturing (or lack there of,) or any other number of factors... but the fact remains that we do not function as you do.<br>
<br>
I understand, why you disagree.  You couldn't possiably understand.  Nor can I.  I have no notion of how you think, or what you feel, other then what you outwardly express.  Not merely words, but actions... or inaction. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Glances over his shoulder at the elf</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
You are as alien to me, as I am to you.<br>
<br>
Perhaps it is the fact that we are so isolated from others, that makes us the way we are.  Perhaps it is the design of our Lord, as we were made in his image.  I lay evidence to the first guess, as seen by many Tier'dal that take residence among the Humans and other races.  They do not act as many other Tier'dal do, for right or wrong.  They think like humans.<br>
<br>
As for our raising of children...  All Tier'dal are creations of our Lord Innoruuk, their birth is a service and testament to him and his power.  Some choose not to serve him.  No matter... They all serve in some way.  Most become warriors for our dispariot king.  Thier service is obvious... the blood they shed breeds hate.  Others reject our Lord outright and walk among so-called-Lightbringers.  These also serve our Lord... in the scorn they suffer from others.  So are they ushered from the cradle to the alter, as you say?  Absolutly.  As well they should.<br>
<br>
This is another thing you can not understand.  You speak to me as if we Tier'dal are to choose a path...  Our lot is given to us.  We are HIS insturment.  We serve HIS whim.  We were not placed with benevolance, to grow and prosper.  We were placed to conqure and war... To spread Innoruuk's will on this world that he can so rarely directly effect.<br>
<br>
I do not hold you accountable for not understanding.<br>
<br>
